      • getAllowedEnumLiteralTexts

        public Map<String,​Map<Class<?>,​Enum<?>>> getAllowedEnumLiteralTexts()
        Description copied from interface: JpaMetamodel
        Returns a map that gives access to the enum literal expressions that can be used in queries. The key is the shorthand enum literal. The value is a map, from enum class to the actual enum value. This is needed for parsing shorthand enum literals that don't use FQNs.
        Specified by:
        getAllowedEnumLiteralTexts in interface JpaMetamodel
